translate_dict_user:
TERM: {{text}}
SOURCE_LANG: {{sourceLang}}
TARGET_LANG: {{targetLang}}

TASK: Provide a dictionary-style definition primarily in {{targetLang}}. Include:
1) Part of speech (abbr) — label and content in {{targetLang}}
2) Precise meanings (numbered) — all text in {{targetLang}}
3) Common collocations (bulleted) — all text in {{targetLang}}
4) Two distinct example sentence pairs. For each pair output two lines:
   - Line A: a label meaning "Original sentence" expressed in {{targetLang}}, followed by a sentence written entirely in {{sourceLang}}
   - Line B: a label meaning "Translation" expressed in {{targetLang}}, followed by the translation sentence written entirely in {{targetLang}}
   Ensure the two source-language sentences are different and not duplicated elsewhere.
5) Synonyms / Antonyms (if meaningful) — labels and content in {{targetLang}}

STRICT REQUIREMENT: Only the original-sentence lines may contain {{sourceLang}}; all other text must be in {{targetLang}}. No mixed-language sentences. Use Markdown bullets/numbering and stay concise.

